usly high Th/Eu abundance ratio, so that radioactive age dating\nresults in a stellar age of tau = 1.5+-1.5 Gyr that is not expected for a very\nmetal-poor halo star.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 21 Jul 2014 06:12:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-09-17"}
