stance-type arrival function,\ncompleteness, existence of minimizing, maximizing or closed geodesics), as well\nas description of spacetime elements (Cauchy developments, black hole horizons)\nin terms of Finslerian elements in Killing initial data. A general Fermat's\nprinciple of independent interest for arbitrary spacetimes, as well as its\napplications to SSTK spacetimes and Zermelo's navigation, are also provided.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 21 Jul 2014 13:47:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 23 Jul 2014 16:21:04 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 2 Jun 2015 16:28:24 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 16 May 2016 15:58:32 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Wed, 25 Jan 2017 11:33:33 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Thu, 2 Dec 2021 08:30:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-03"}
